{
  "analysis": "We are in /app with no prior outputs shown. The task is to speed up MuJoCo simulation of a given MJCF model (/app/model_ref.xml) to 60% of original runtime or less, for 2 seconds of simulation, while maintaining identical physics state within atol=1e-5 and avoiding NaN/Inf. We must not alter physical properties; the tuned model should be saved at /app/model.xml. There is an /app/eval.py script to help iterate. We need to inspect the repository to understand eval.py and the MJCF model structure, then attempt safe optimizations that do not alter physics, such as disabling assets that affect rendering only, adjusting compiler or sizes that affect performance but not physics, and possibly adjusting contact settings that are equivalent numerically. First, list files, view eval.py to see exact checks and allowed changes, then open model_ref.xml to understand content. Then make a copy to /app/model.xml and attempt modifications. Then run eval.py to benchmark and verify correctness.",
